Oct 27 2009 	great deal for a good hotel	After reading some of these reviews, I was hesitant in booking here. My choices were limited, so I did. Pleasantly surprised. Clean, nice entrance foyer, friendly staff, comfortable beds/rooms. No complaints at all. The hotel is old and helps give it the character that makes it what it is. No smells or other problems that I have read about. I was not expecting a 4 star - I was expecting a 3 star and that is what the Opal San Francisco is. Location is not a problem at all. Everyone wants to ride the trolley anyway, so just turn right out of the hotel and walk a few short blocks to California St. That is where the trolley starts and will take you on a fun ride straight into Union Square. From there you can go anywhere. We like higher end hotels but they were not available for the time were were visiting. The Opal San Francisco was a nice alternative.	
