Aug 21 2009 	clean 	Centrally located on a major road through the city, The Opal was clean and comfortable and reserving online made the hotel a good deal. However, housekeeping was very stingy with amenities like shampoo and soap...we had to ask more than once, and the quality of them was mediocre. Ceramic cups and glasses in the rooms instead of paper/plastic would have been a huge improvement (and probably save the hotel money and the planet's landfills over time). The beds were quite comfy and nicely appointed with linens. Desk staff helpfulness was inconsistent - some of them were snooty &amp; not terribly helpful, some of them were really great and eager to make suggestions and give directions. Parking in the back was convenient and secure, &amp; needs to be in this neighborhood. The lobby very nicely renovated, and although the complimentary breakfast was good, it was extremely crowded and disorganized. Overall, though, for the price, we would stay there again.	
