n my legs and back. It has been three weeks and I am still healing. I have ongoing histimic reactions to the bites. The worst part is there is nothing a person can do, but take antihistimine (very bad for the liver) and keep covered in ointments. Please be warned that you are endangering yourself and/ or friends. This is a very serious issue.	
Aug 8 2009	Comfy Cozy and good location	We spent 4 nights here in early August 2009 with a group tour from France. The staff were on their toes and very helpful. The lobby is tastefully decorated and well appointed - a comfortable place to &quot;chill out&quot;. ATM right behind the lobby as well as a laundry room, which can come in very handy. Wifi in the lobby area. Coffee/tea bar tastefully hidden in a little nook in the lobby. Our room was clean and comfortable, featured high-speed internet connection (with RJ45 plug). The breakfast buffet was more than adequate (bread, bagels, raisin bread + big toasters), but closes at 9am. Unfortunately, this means that by 8:30am there's nothing much left to eat. Do as we did, gather up your courage and go downstairs before 8am, fix your breakfast and take it back to your room! We saw lots of people doing this...If you miss your breakfast, there's always the diner next door (with a direct access from the lobby), or a bakery a block away from the hotel (exit right, leaving the hotel), with a huge array of donuts and hot breakfasts (eggs, bacon, pancakes). HOWEVER. Please do be careful with the homeless people in the area. Our tour guide had her suitcase stolen from the sidewalk in front of the hotel - but managed to get it back with the help of 3 guys from our group and a small &quot;tip&quot; to the homeless guy. This seems to be a recurrent problem in the area as there is a homeless shelter 1-2 blocks away from the hotel. Nothing to freak out over - just don't leave any bags unattended.Convenient location. MUNI (bus) in front of the hotel - and on both streets north and south of the hotel. Get a 1 or 3 day pass and a map. I read the comment from a previous blog about &quot;bed bug&quot; problem and was very concerned about this. I checked the Bed Bugs Registry (www.bedbugregistry.com). This hotel is indeed on the list, as are most of the hotels in the area. I'm happy to say that neither we nor anyone else in our group of 41 experienced a bed bug problem.Overall, the hotel was much better than expected.	
