May 28 2009 	better than expected	Note: the ratings should be 3.5, but I rounded up. Basically this was our only choice through my sister's points to get 2 suite rooms for 3 nights (for free) in san fran. I normally try to get 4 star hotels through priceline or vacation pkg deals like expedia. The suite rooms are bigger than the standard in that there is a sofa and coffee table. This &quot;living room&quot; area is not separated from the 2 beds. It's just 1 bigger room. There's a Mel's Drive-In attached next to the hotel. My sister ate there and said it was just okay, but note she's not that crazy about greasy food. Everything was to expectations for a 3 star hotel. The windows are double paned (soundproof?). We opened the window in both the room and bathroom because the weather was so nice, but since our windows faced the back/parking lot, sometimes you could smell the cigarette smoke outside below. The hotel does provide complimentary internet. Our room also had the flat screen LCD tv. You can hear people talking as they pass your door through the hallway, but that is to be expected. They do have a laundry room with 1 washer and 1 dryer across from the fitness room. There seems to be only 1 elevator by the front but we took the stairs once we discovered them since our room was on the very next floor. If you want to rent a car, there's an enterprise nearby, 1133 Van Ness Ave, but you can easily travel on the public transportation. I used this website: http://tripplanner.transit.511.org/mtc/XSLT_TRIP_REQUEST2?language=en to map out the bus routes. The bus stops themselves have a digital sign that shows how many minutes the next bus will arrive. We also took the BART to/from the SFO airport (www.bart.gov) - it's only $5.35 one way. You get off at the civic center. Then it's less than a mile to the hotel (12-15 min walk). Larkin street is very closeby and has a lot of vietnamese restaurants (5 min walk). Took the bus to the restaurant Thanh Long for their famous garlic noodles and roast crab.	
